               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donors; name of the king; a few lines on the incipit page of the Text, alternating with black lines; incipit of each section of the text; names of Hebrew letters in Ps. 118; abbreviations; some other words: e.g., halle luya (e.g., fols. 9rb, 24vb), ṣällǝyu (e.g., fol. 14rb), wä-kaʿǝbä (e.g., fols. 14vb, 15rb), wä-yǝbälu (e.g., fols. 19rb, 19vb), ʾǝgäle (e.g., fols. 25rb, 96ra), qǝdmä wangel (e.g., fols. 30ra, 53va); elements of Ethiopic numerals; elements of the punctuation signs and text dividers.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
